{
  "stem": "27150.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You see, that means in the Hebrew School, you see, we never-- we were among the Jews, you see.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was Jewish, too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "L'Or, L'Or-- L-A-- or L apostrophe O-R.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is 'to light' in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a Friedman, or something.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Jewish name, you see, because there was a lot of, of Jewish teachers, you see, Jewish nationals, you see, that means, teaching in Polish.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So while Tarbut was a Hebrew school-- that means it is science and accounts and art or anything was in Hebrew, you see-- the other Jewish private high schools, they were taught Polish, other than two lessons in Hebrew, you see, as a second language, as a foreign language.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a foreign language, French or German, and you had to pick one.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "French.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we, we didn't feel very much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see, the question is that it was hard to get to university-- for Poles, too-- unless they had good marks.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, that means in '29-- you-- '28, '29-- you see, the thing was coming.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They decided that Robin will go to a commercial college, which kept the top classes of high school with other-- you see, instead of Latin and maths, or something, there were emphasis of, accounting and correspondence and economic geography.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, chemistry was switched over to merchandise quality, science, and it was a very good school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a year later, I joined the same school, a class lower, and this was a very good school run by the Chamber of Commerce.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you had to have connections to get in, of course.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, actually my uncle, who died in New York--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Akiwa.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A-K-I-W-A.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Akiwa, that means-- it's a Hebrew name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We called him Kuba.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
